                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1598" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE LAWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a wheelright, of Lambeth-wall. I met the prisoner Brady, and went with her to the Elephant and Castle, and then to a house—I had 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—three sovereigns were in my waistcoat-pocket—Brady wanted me to go in—I would not—she unbuttoned my coat and took them out—I caught her by the shawl—Beasley came up, and said, "If you don't let that woman go I will knock your b----y eyes out"—I am sure Brady's hand was in my pocket—I had my money safe ten minutes before—I had my hand upon it.</p>
